Senate Chief Whip, Orji Uzor Kalu has congratulated the Senate Deputy Minority Leader, Senator Emmanuel Bwacha for dumping the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, for the ruling All Progressives Congress, APC. DAILY POST had reported that Senator Bwacha was officially received into the party by President Muhammadu Buhari on Thursday in Aso Rock Villa, Abuja. Senator Orji Kalu in a post on his official Facebook page, hailed his fellow lawmaker for the courage to dump the opposition party as 2023 general elections draw near. The former governor of Abia State said he looks forward to the contribution of the Deputy Minority Leader to the development of the ruling party. He said, Congratulations to the Senate Deputy Minority Leader, Senator Emmanuel Bwacha, who has joined the All Progressives Congress (APC) from the Peoples Democratic Party. “I applaud his decision and I look forward to his contributions to the development of our party”.